 by the JDK `java.xml` module.\\n\\nFix applied in:\\n\\n- `tests/src/xerces/xmlParserAPIs/2.6.2/src/test/java/xerces/xmlParserAPIs/JavaxXmlParsersSecuritySupportTest.java`\\n\\nWhat changed:\\n\\n- Added a small dedicated `XmlParserApisClassLoader` that loads the `xmlParserAPIs` copy of:\\n  - `javax.xml.parsers.SecuritySupport`\\n  - `javax.xml.parsers.SecuritySupport12...`\\n- The test now loads the active class from the library JAR class bytes instead of asking the JDK/application class loader for it.\\n- Wrapped dynamic class loading with the required Native Image unsupported-feature handling via:\\n  - `NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)`\\n\\nThis should resolve the JVM failure while still exercising the two intended dynamic-access resource call sites.\", \"textSignature\": \"{\\\"v\\\":1,\\\"id\\\":\\\"msg_0bb5d39a304e23be0169f8f8d3756481948180f769d85fb412\\\",\\\"phase\\\":\\\"final_answer\\\"}\"}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 1267, \"output\": 1253, \"cacheRead\": 46080, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 48600, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"stop\", \"timestamp\": 1777924289380, \"responseId\": \"resp_0bb5d39a304e23be0169f8f8c224148194b7a1253c3315a754\"}}\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge8/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/logs/xerces:xmlParserAPIs:2.6.2/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-04T19-50-15-271532Z.log:8783:[recv] {\"type\": \"turn_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Considering native image resources**\\n\\nIt seems there's an issue where the resource from the dependency jar isn't included in the native image without proper metadata about class resources. Since we don't add that metadata, calling getParent().getResourceAsStream might return null, resulting in a ClassNotFoundException that isn't caught. Hmm, for unsupported features, maybe we should try getting a resource from our own test resources to see how that behaves.\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_0bb5d39a304e23be0169f8f8c2e9288194b0367131e7c1308d\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABp-PjTqFT8UBJrM1_we3c5PgDm8IyKYeGbVPmiAR0-Diozylb1A2x3MTYavcoJpNmywL2dykan9gIWNYYhk3JiZpJ_A3m7-ZTKqznQP0ImnXpvNzgx4Vrh7WO3PmTbMXTCWomOxByUA9_cAtWwr-RieuE7it4nBMNsYCR0DvPzOZkyW7Hk8Fp7Hw6acAKjAqEkJs0pQ1YRRAJb8z2Afk3cC0rfXE82W5dqeGFW-uwWSAdyqIUGpZ1nqnPMfcJmb944X_C4EkEmmYicStYziWO3DU04qTIrwDuo3kzMpkBIs1MiWOwTwj_d31LnqnN5z34jjS3M4ZjIAzooWjG91pFaS88L-R_9dWi6cbPA9gI5Xn3Wc5tncOb4p8u8BBAqTdr379llxSHzMnVSVatzckMbp4VKbkBak7-wFXpEyZ4SQsIScb_5E2kM_GOx26SlAQcV6myJ4SMFwnHxoFQPEDPX_7I6NWccqWrZSlPae4-DRkgqjEk-mWJd-mSg7QQVZSYvM9wHE5deS7tdJnlllJbpJvNxZvcLP3fGpKO04i6ZU1kcEyzLEEXsxoOkv5y1L3n_bByBKDZdB07Oj0xHYs0sw9QIqEMnuXFq2tAO8khsHDUsG-02oZuoKsXmcUspxsUsPfh9ln__jY-fjG1SLCt_N0UtRDvnKJ3pNCzk4cu8TgJcd4L7Nkn0TG4uSKkSTR4vVwXthYAtb3y9t3AOngzD3f5J_xU2Ra92kcN_IqtpVCrusQ1Y8XNxSsCzcQmSWi7Pdm5ZUnmVfOZ_bC0U2TopZ2u84utfmx3RkHn1-LP2lprPAQg9rE8dHNWWvk27imAYaaky-1qsEtWYYvqT9B1oaypdov_Hl4twKgOWs4d_DX-2qTcBiVttoVfX3X7j7i9Dc4juJ-8bY10lsJNMZYY5tCKbluLLsIubdGHT_HtOyX64ykgcfbbzg_LxLyzoO_DMvilyPOrfBaaT0Vu_Hh8NOVZn3wGBsBUWcJcVkOv2hI_zg8e25EVeJSDkRNymx-oxU_onE9_dl4I-iNX96MIvRpCDn1-iGqVYlJtsxVBWKEGFq6VUMZ_3ri1ngdo20VpSaVuVyhFWr4kG1km_1WB-J8pfCpR95L8AiD5tWciBXRKEml4DYOlJfgOrL-0OSvb3lKKTnMb0tJm-pCnlMUPt6rRALlyoXIGLE7zqq0CHac3c6-9V_tH0uFZudb0ndEuJ0jrwSzai5DVNdI7jgsrHr2DbYbqcpjbooC59N2hgsd4R7fx2dAn0t4TLEQjy9q700SrvGew1fK7DLphkEFUutadEdSvF672snVL0qeuo9C4-UoTvM2ZfKR1NpZJVhYSfao9HhFDz5g2gEg-bef30Zh58TaEp5L1H7ZPgnUJHF6u4TQLbQAm0ccOftgHEKftX3TSwwGQf-JHzcgFsunu4FYUfI3AKtTTc0gl1v7N7s56eh3yiR9nv_WzWF60W-GdD_amSpaGvO1WN4453Xc_ZsnoW12nUZTgcahP7brL5xbepc4zghmW5_7fEA__4LnTBUeSvbnqMGJ59wF9ou6M4YK4R1LsDOJIcjX63EvrzWFy9JSAS_S0zlOTRuovSNcWA0rY5p1PmXYi6eA11ebPNf7HT8KDxNFi6TMZsWsI385VCF4xvLr1ae2P86YjSg2AijxJVUCi_DPnu7rfHn29zMdgx7idvYZFM0HWftF5o8